<div class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-snippet wprm-recipe-template-jump-only"><a href="#recipe" data-recipe="165476" style="color: #333333;" class="wprm-recipe-jump wprm-recipe-link wprm-jump-to-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-jump-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="#333333" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,6.5 8,11 12.5,6.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> JUMP TO RECIPE</a></div><input class="jpibfi" type="hidden">
<p><strong>Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies</strong> are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on a dessert table, and they go perfectly with <a href="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-valentine-cookies/" data-wpel-link="internal"><strong>Nutter Butter Valentine Cookies</strong></a>. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, edible work of art using bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. They’re ideal for Valentine’s Day parties, after-school treats, or holiday dessert trays.</p>



<p>The best part about these &#8220;love bugs&#8221; is that they&#8217;re a completely no-bake recipe. You don’t have to worry about preheating the oven or measuring flour; you just melt, dip, and decorate. Kids will enjoy decorating the sweet and salty treats as much as they will love eating them. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A wide overhead shot of six Nutter Butter love bug cookies spread across parchment paper with scattered pink hearts and a red scarf." class="wp-image-165466" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg" alt="A wide overhead shot of six Nutter Butter love bug cookies spread across parchment paper with scattered pink hearts and a red scarf." class="wp-image-165466" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies-with-overlay.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>I can&#8217;t believe how adorable these Love Bug Nutter Butters turned out, and the family devoured them.  I may have to make them again in February, along with some <a href="https://blogghetti.com/strawberry-white-chocolate-bark/" data-wpel-link="internal">Strawberry White Chocolate Bark</a>. Maybe I&#8217;ll even surprise the family with a few <a href="https://blogghetti.com/cinnamon-roll-hearts/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cinnamon Roll Hearts</a> for breakfast, too. These treats are a perfect way to share a little extra sweetness with my favorite people.</p>



