toc-heading-12" href="#Nutritional_Disclaimer">Nutritional Disclaimer</a></li></ul></li></ul></nav></div>
<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Nutter_Butter_Love_Bug_Cookies"></span>Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>These easy-to-make love bug cookies come together by dipping peanut butter cookies in colorful candy melts, stacking them to create a playful “bug” shape, and decorating them with sprinkles, pretzel antennae, and candy details.</p>



<p>The process may feel more like crafting than baking, making it easy to get creative with each cookie. Every love bug ends up with its own personality, which is part of what makes this recipe so fun to make and share.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Timesaving_Tips_and_Variations"></span>Timesaving Tips and Variations<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>Decorating these cookies is the most fun part, but a little prep makes the process smoother and less messy. Having all your ingredients within reach helps keep things moving quickly.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Use a fork or candy dipping tool to coat cookies evenly and reduce cleanup.</li>



<li>Do a few at a time so the melted chocolate is easy to work with when adding decorations.</li>



<li>Swap pink candy melts for red or white to match your theme.</li>



<li>Break pretzel sticks ahead of time to speed up assembly.</li>



<li>Use different themed candies for several different looks.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A person's hand holding up a completed Nutter Butter love bug cookie to show its size and decorative candy details." class="wp-image-165463" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg" alt="A person's hand holding up a completed Nutter Butter love bug cookie to show its size and decorative candy details." class="wp-image-165463" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hand-holding-cookie-bug.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>These simple swaps and tips help you cruise through the assembly line and have your masterpieces looking super adorable. </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Other_Sweet_Treats_to_Serve_with_Your_Love_Bugs"></span>Other Sweet Treats to Serve with Your Love Bugs<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>These decorated treats are definitely the star of the show, but they play well with a few other treats on the side.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://blogghetti.com/easy-valentines-day-brownies/" data-wpel-link="internal">Valentine’s Day Brownies</a></li>



<li><a href="https://www.redcottagechronicles.com/recipe/chocolate-fruit-pizza/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Chocolate Fruit Pizza</a></li>



<li><a href="https://blogghetti.com/slow-cooker-hot-chocolate-recipe/" data-wpel-link="internal">Slow Cooker Hot Chocolate Recipe</a></li>



<li><a href="https://familyaroundthetable.com/strawberry-cake-mix-cookies/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-wpel-link="external">Strawberry Cake Mix Cookies</a></li>



<li><a href="https://blogghetti.com/valentines-day-frosted-sugar-cookies/" data-wpel-link="internal">Valentine’s Day Frosted Sugar Cookies</a></li>
</ul>



<p>Whether you go for a refreshing fruit plate or a creamy drink, these simple additions will make your Valentine’s celebration feel extra special and well-thought-out.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Six Nutter Butter love bug cookies arranged on white parchment paper decorated with pink glitter hearts and a red heart-patterned fabric background." class="wp-image-165457" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg" alt="Six Nutter Butter love bug cookies arranged on white parchment paper decorated with pink glitter hearts and a red heart-patterned fabric background." class="wp-image-165457" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/6-nutter-butter-cookies-for-valentines-day.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-frequently-asked-questions"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Frequently_Asked_Questions"></span>Frequently Asked Questions<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1769619071846"><strong class="schema-faq-question">What if I don’t have all the candy decorations?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">No problem! You can swap in similar candies, chocolate chips, or even mini marshmallows. Creativity is part of the fun, and each love bug will have its own personality.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1769619486327"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Can kids help make them?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Absolutely. Kids can add sprinkles, place the eyes, and decorate the little love bugs. An adult should handle the melted candy to keep things safe.</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1769619536234"><strong class="schema-faq-question">Do the nutter butters need to be refrigerated?</strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Refrigeration isn’t necessary and can sometimes create condensation on the candy coating. Room temperature storage in a cool, dry spot works best to keep them looking their best.</p> </div> </div>



