ata-jpibfi-src="https://easyproductdisplays.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/231.png" ></noscript></a></p><p style="clear:both;font-size:0;">&nbsp;</p>



<p>With these tools on hand, the process and cleanup are easier, and you’ll be able to focus on creating adorable little love bugs that everyone will adore.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A close-up of a love bug cookie decorated with two red heart sprinkles on its body, resting on white parchment paper next to a pink glitter heart." class="wp-image-165465" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg" alt="A close-up of a love bug cookie decorated with two red heart sprinkles on its body, resting on white parchment paper next to a pink glitter heart." class="wp-image-165465" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookie-with-red-hearts.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="Ingredients_Needed_for_Nutter_Butter_Love_Bug_Cookies"></span>Ingredients Needed for Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>This recipe uses simple, easy-to-find ingredients that come together to give your little critters personality and charm.</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong><a href="https://walmrt.us/3Z1OIzk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener sponsored nofollow" data-wpel-link="external">Nutter Butter cookies</a></strong> – the classic base for each love bug</li>



<li><strong>Pink and white candy melts</strong> – for coating, stacking, and adding color</li>



<li><strong>Sprinkles (red, white, pink)</strong> for decorating the wings</li>



<li><strong>Jumbo hearts)</strong> – for decorating</li>



<li><strong>Pretzel sticks</strong> – to make the antennas</li>



<li><strong>Candy eyeballs and mini chocolate chips</strong> – for eyes and nose details</li>



<li><strong> M&amp;Ms</strong> – fun accents for the lower part of the body</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="An overhead shot of the recipe ingredients including a package of Nutter Butters, bowls of pink and white candy melts, pretzels, sprinkles, and candy eyes." class="wp-image-165464" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg" alt="An overhead shot of the recipe ingredients including a package of Nutter Butters, bowls of pink and white candy melts, pretzels, sprinkles, and candy eyes." class="wp-image-165464" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/ingredients-for-cookies.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>Having everything ready before you start makes assembly much smoother. Once you lay out your ingredients, decorating becomes the best part of the process.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-how-to-make-nutter-butter-love-bugs"><span class="ez-toc-section" id="How_to_Make_Nutter_Butter_Love_Bugs"></span>How to Make Nutter Butter Love Bugs<span class="ez-toc-section-end"></span></h2>



<p>Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Melt pink and white candy melts in separate microwave-safe bowls. Dip a Nutter Butter in pink candy melts, tap off excess, and add a few sprinkles to the sides, leaving the center clear. Let set until the chocolate is firm to the touch.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A three-panel collage showing a Nutter Butter cookie being dipped in pink candy melts and topped with sprinkles to create the love bug wings." class="wp-image-165459" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg" alt="A three-panel collage showing a Nutter Butter cookie being dipped in pink candy melts and topped with sprinkles to create the love bug wings." class="wp-image-165459" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/creating-the-wings.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>Coat another Nutter Butter in white candy melts and place it crosswise on top of the pink cookie. Add pretzel antennas, candy eyes, a chocolate chip nose, and finish with M&amp;Ms or heart sprinkles. Let set until firm and then store in an airtight container at room temperature until needed.  </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%20900%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A three-panel process collage showing broken pretzel sticks, a white-coated cookie being placed on pink wings, and the final facial details being added." class="wp-image-165461" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body.jpg 1200w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="900" height="1200" data-pin-nopin="true" src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg" alt="A three-panel process collage showing broken pretzel sticks, a white-coated cookie being placed on pink wings, and the final facial details being added." class="wp-image-165461" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-900x1200.jpg 900w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-225x300.jpg 225w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-640x853.jpg 640w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body-150x200.jpg 150w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/decorating-the-bug-body.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px" /></noscript></figure>



<p>Looking for more sweet treats to make your celebration extra fun? Try pairing these tasty bites with these <a href="https://blogghetti.com/small-batch-chocolate-cupcakes/" data-wpel-link="internal">Small Batch Chocolate Cupcakes</a> for a mix of flavors and textures that everyone will love.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="900" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20900'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A wide overhead shot of six Nutter Butter love bug cookies spread across parchment paper with scattered pink hearts and a red scarf." class="wp-image-165468" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg 1200w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-300x225.jpg 300w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-768x576.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-500x375.jpg 500w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-150x113.jpg 150w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg" /><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="900" data-pin-description="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies are the kind of festive, no-bake treat that instantly grabs attention on any snack spread. They take a classic peanut butter cookie and turn it into a tiny, colorful creation with bright candy melts and fun sprinkles. The best part is they’re completely no-bake—you just melt, dip, and decorate—and kids will have as much fun making them as they do eating them." src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg" alt="A wide overhead shot of six Nutter Butter love bug cookies spread across parchment paper with scattered pink hearts and a red scarf." class="wp-image-165468" data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://blogghetti.com/nutter-butter-love-bug-cookies/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Nutter Butter Love Bug Cookies" data-jpibfi-src="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg" srcset="https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs.jpg 1200w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-300x225.jpg 300w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-768x576.jpg 768w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-500x375.jpg 500w, https://blogghetti.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/overhead-view-of-cute-cookie-bugs-150x113.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></figure>


